Next, we utilized the average sliding window correlation (ASWC) to improve the robustness of correlation coefficient estimations and to minimize the loss of temporal resolution (compared to e.g. a sliding window correlation approach). ASWC averages a predefined number of consecutive sliding window correlations (SWCs) and then advances one step and averages the next set of SWCs for dFC (22 s window length), which resulted in 284 (LEMON) and 198 (SALD) final correlation matrices containing \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
